                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d920">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7652</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Letcher</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 6, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Recent press despatches state American employees National Mines and Smelter
                    Company, Magistral, Durango, disarmed, and Magistral looted.</p>
                <p>Endeavor ascertain whether report correct. If Americans at Magistral in personal
                    danger, or such danger threatened, advise them to leave that place.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
